 you better keep away
with your hands 

05:35.502 --> 05:37.903
 don't even try it 

05:37.904 --> 05:40.305
Now that's what
I'm talking about.
 say good night 

05:40.307 --> 05:44.576
 say good-bye,
don't even try 

05:53.520 --> 05:55.387
Roscoe: Anybody
can learn to dance.

05:55.389 --> 05:59.491
Trust me, roscoe.
You don't wanna
go there.

05:59.493 --> 06:01.226
Ok, nobody's perfect, ok?

06:01.228 --> 06:02.828
Oh, ok.

06:02.830 --> 06:04.730
It's not just
the dancing anyway, sam.

06:04.732 --> 06:06.765
It's attitude, personality.

06:06.767 --> 06:09.167
Yeah, it's
an inner connection
to the music.

06:09.169 --> 06:10.268
I've got a connection.

06:10.270 --> 06:12.437
After all, I write the songs...

06:12.439 --> 06:14.740
And a real personality.

06:15.376 --> 06:17.342
Well, no one cares about real.

06:17.344 --> 06:20.078
They want larger than life.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.648
She's right, sam.

06:26.453 --> 06:30.355
There's way too much
negative energy here.

06:41.435 --> 06:43.034
Hey.

06:43.370 --> 06:45.370
Writin' down some new lyrics?

06:45.372 --> 06:47.406
Yeah. Can you think
of anything

06:47.408 --> 06:50.475
That rhymes with
pain and misery?

06:55.416 --> 06:57.582
Hey. All the years
we've been friends,

06:57.584 --> 07:00.051
Have I ever
given you bad advice?

07:00.053 --> 07:01.987
Always.

07:01.989 --> 07:05.323
So I'm due for some good advice.

07:09.596 --> 07:10.629
Look...

07:10.631 --> 07:11.963
You write awesome songs.

07:11.965 --> 07:14.232
Maybe it's just time
you let someone else
sing them...

07:14.234 --> 07:18.236
An addition to the band,
not a replacement.

07:18.238 --> 07:20.539
Oh.

07:22.309 --> 07:23.975
Ok.

07:26.447 --> 07:28.079
Here.

07:29.316 --> 07:30.816
Save this.

07:31.251 --> 07:32.150
Your original lyric sheets

07:32.152 --> 07:34.453
Will be worth a fortune someday.

07:34.455 --> 07:36.354
See, that's what I like
about you, roscoe.

07:36.356 --> 07:39.691
You're always...

07:39.693 --> 07:40.826
Looking to the future.

07:40.828 --> 07:43.495
Yeah, tell my father.

07:43.497 --> 07:45.697
To him, my vision
is never grand enough.

07:45.699 --> 07:49.434
I wish there was some secret

07:49.436 --> 07:52.504
To being everything
people wanted us to be.

07:53.974 --> 07:54.873
Yeah, well...

07:54.875 --> 07:56.208
Until someone
bottles perfection,

07:56.210 --> 07:59.010
I guess we're stuck
with what we've got.

08:04.618 --> 08:07.652
So how are things
in your part of the world?

08:07.654 --> 08:09.020
All right, I guess.

08:09.022 --> 08:10.689
Things are
a little rough
for sam right now.

08:10.691 --> 08:14.226
Mmm. I couldn't think
of a more perfect match.

08:16.230 --> 08:20.031
Dad, sam and I are just friends.

08:20.033 --> 08:21.199
So what's the problem?

08:21.201 --> 08:22.167
I don't know.

08:22.169 --> 08:24.202
I mean, she's fun to be with.

08:24.204 --> 08:25.704
But she gets so moody.

08:25.706 --> 08:29.241
She's talented.
But she can be
so stubborn.

08:29.243 --> 08:31.910
I like her. But...

08:32.679 --> 08:33.812
See?
That's the problem.

08:33.813 --> 08:36.147
How do you get past
all those buts?

08:36.149 --> 08:37.515
Ship them off to china.

08:37.518 --> 08:39.484
What?

08:39.486 --> 08:41.352
Overnight. Every
last one of 'em. We...

08:41.355 --> 08:42.386
They... they need
the technology.

08:42.389 --> 08:46.324
We've got a surplus.
It's a match made in heaven.

08:47.327 --> 08:48.360
Thanks for the help.

08:48.362 --> 08:51.229
What?

08:52.766 --> 08:55.667
So, you have a good day, huh?

08:59.506 --> 09:01.840
Nice tone, luv.
But can you move?

09:10.083 --> 09:11.449
Nice tone.

09:11.451 --> 09:14.753
Nice tone.
But can you move?

09:14.755 --> 09:15.755
Move.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.093
All right.
Oh, my god.

09:22.095 --> 09:25.363
Just take it... god.

09:26.533 --> 09:27.866
Ok, which version?

09:27.868 --> 09:30.168
Yes! Ok.

09:37.878 --> 09:39.578
Roscoe: Yes!

