17:27.914 --> 17:29.113
Who you talking to?

17:29.115 --> 17:32.417
Uh, no one, no one.
My-my-myself.

17:34.220 --> 17:35.820
Huh.

17:41.194 --> 17:42.527
Wow.

17:44.597 --> 17:45.563
Impressive.

17:45.565 --> 17:49.033
Yeah. Yeah, well,
it's... it's just a hand.

17:49.035 --> 17:50.635
Well, why don't we
team up and work
on this together?

17:50.637 --> 17:51.736
I... I don't...
I don't need help.

17:51.738 --> 17:52.703
I just think that I could...

17:52.705 --> 17:55.306
Maybe some...
Some other time.

17:55.775 --> 17:57.375
All right, fine.

18:07.287 --> 18:08.970
Roscoe: It's simple, max.

18:08.971 --> 18:10.654
All you have to do is plug in
the quadratic formula,

18:10.657 --> 18:12.774
And solve for "x."

18:12.775 --> 18:14.892
How can I do that?
I don't know what "x" is.

18:14.894 --> 18:16.928
Come on, max.

18:16.930 --> 18:18.396
Your mother's
the head of skygraph.

18:18.398 --> 18:21.499
Some of those brains
must have trickled down.

18:24.838 --> 18:27.572
Well, you keep workin' on this.

18:27.574 --> 18:28.339
I'll be right back.

18:28.341 --> 18:31.175
Wait!
Where are you goin'?

18:31.177 --> 18:33.311
Come on!
What's more important,

18:33.313 --> 18:36.681
Some girl or my math test?

18:36.683 --> 18:38.282
Roscoe: Sam, wait up.

18:38.284 --> 18:39.284
Hi.

18:39.285 --> 18:40.385
Hey.

18:40.386 --> 18:41.486
I haven't seen you all week.

18:41.487 --> 18:42.587
Yeah, well, you know,
I've been workin'
pretty hard

18:42.589 --> 18:43.921
Fine-tuning loretta.

18:43.923 --> 18:47.391
I want her to be just right
