That's 4,335 matches.

55:54.518 --> 55:57.419
<i>No way out, way out west,</i>

55:57.421 --> 56:00.756
Way out on a limb.
Ha ha ha!

56:05.396 --> 56:08.063
Oh!

56:10.167 --> 56:11.667
Hey, are you looking
to refinance?

56:11.669 --> 56:13.869
We've got the lowest
mortgage rates!

56:13.871 --> 56:15.504
Huh, huh?
What do you say?

56:15.506 --> 56:17.272
Get lost!

56:22.213 --> 56:23.545
I hate pop-up ads.

56:23.547 --> 56:28.150
Pop! Pop! Pop!
I hate 'em,
I hate 'em.

56:29.420 --> 56:33.021
Ok, hold on.

56:41.465 --> 56:43.799
What's that over there?

56:43.801 --> 56:45.701
That? A server.

56:45.703 --> 56:48.937
Pretty big one
by the look of it.

56:50.274 --> 56:51.373
Hey, what are you doing?

56:51.375 --> 56:55.177
Hey, you don't want to go there!

57:25.810 --> 57:27.242
E-mail.

57:27.244 --> 57:31.079
I can attach myself
to an e-mail.

57:31.081 --> 57:33.982
I just need to find
the right one.

57:34.785 --> 57:38.854
Excuse me. Is this
sorted alphabetically

57:38.856 --> 57:39.988
Or by domain?

57:39.990 --> 57:41.423
Virus alert, virus alert!

57:41.425 --> 57:43.258
What?

57:45.463 --> 57:47.429
Oh!

57:55.639 --> 57:57.339
Oh.

57:59.210 --> 58:01.777
Hello?

58:01.779 --> 58:04.713
Can anyone help me?

58:04.715 --> 58:07.049
I'm lost.

58:23.033 --> 58:24.183
Name?

58:24.184 --> 58:25.334
Loretta modern.
I need to find...

58:25.336 --> 58:27.870
Do you have
an e-mail address?

58:27.872 --> 58:29.805
Yes.

58:32.676 --> 58:34.710
We cannot be held responsible

58:34.712 --> 58:36.078
For any accidental deletions,

58:36.080 --> 58:39.815
Power surges,
or data corruptions.

58:39.817 --> 58:41.216
Mm-hmm.

58:43.320 --> 58:45.821
Yeow! Aah!

58:47.691 --> 58:50.526
Computer: You have
a new message.

58:50.528 --> 58:53.161
Loretta:
Samantha, help me!

58:53.163 --> 58:55.297
What?

59:00.337 --> 59:01.570
It's me... loretta!

59:01.572 --> 59:06.174
Uhh! Roscoe e-mailed
you to me?

59:06.176 --> 59:07.176
I was only kidding.

59:07.177 --> 59:08.944
Quick, plug in my data cell.

59:08.946 --> 59:11.613
Uhh. Oh, fine.

59:11.615 --> 59:13.782
If roscoe wants to play games,

59:13.784 --> 59:17.286
I can play games, too.

59:20.357 --> 59:24.359
There you are, loretta.
Safe and sound.

59:24.361 --> 59:27.229
And you can stay there
till the next ice age

59:27.231 --> 59:29.998
For all I care.

59:49.887 --> 59:51.587
Where's samantha?

59:51.589 --> 59:56.224
She's inside. Whoa,
slow down, roscoe.

01:00:02.232 --> 01:00:03.999
Loretta's gone.

01:00:04.001 --> 01:00:05.601
Gone? What do
you mean gone?

01:00:05.603 --> 01:00:07.769
We had a fight.
She went into the net.

01:00:07.771 --> 01:00:11.273
What did you tell her?
"my way or the information
superhighway?"

01:00:11.275 --> 01:00:12.741
I don't think you get it.

01:00:12.743 --> 01:00:14.626
The internet's like
a tornado for her.

01:00:14.627 --> 01:00:16.510
She could be shredded
between a thousand
different servers.

01:00:16.513 --> 01:00:18.080
I'm sure she can
take care of herself.

01:00:18.082 --> 01:00:20.148
I was up all night
trying to trace her.

01:00:20.150 --> 01:00:21.950
What's the band
gonna do
without her?

01:00:21.952 --> 01:00:24.486
It's not about the band.

01:00:24.488 --> 01:00:26.421
It's about you.

01:00:26.423 --> 01:00:28.090
What?

01:00:28.092 --> 01:00:29.691
You're in love with her.

01:00:29.693 --> 01:00:32.995
Don't be ridiculous.

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:35.097
Of course you are.

01:00:35.099 --> 01:00:39.368
You designed her to be
your perfect girl.

01:00:39.370 --> 01:00:41.870
How could you help
but fall in love with her?

01:00:41.872 --> 01:00:43.939
She can sing, she can dance,

01:00:43.941 --> 01:00:47.109
She's funny and beautiful.

01:00:47.111 --> 01:00:49.444
But you know what, roscoe?

01:00:49.446 --> 01:00:51.613
She's not real.

01:00:54.051 --> 01:00:57.052
What is real, anyway?

01:00:58.122 --> 01:01:01.189
Me. I'm real.

01:01:01.191 --> 01:01:03.225
And I'm right here.

01:01:03.727 --> 01:01:07.896
I've always been right here.

01:01:14.171 --> 01:01:17.939
Sam, I...

01:01:18.375 --> 01:01:20.308
I've got her.

01:01:20.310 --> 01:01:21.310
What?

01:01:21.311 --> 01:01:23.845
Loretta. She found
her way to my computer.

01:01:23.847 --> 01:01:25.981
Well, then she's ok?

01:01:28.352 --> 01:01:31.386
She's fine.

01:01:36.760 --> 01:01:40.395
Oh!

01:01:40.898 --> 01:01:43.565
I'll leave you two alone.

01:02:01.518 --> 01:02:03.785
Thank you.

01:02:03.787 --> 01:02:08.590
You, uh, remember
the last thing
susan said to you?

01:02:08.592 --> 01:02:10.358
What?

01:02:10.360 --> 01:02:14.696
Susan.
Your last girlfriend.

01:02:14.698 --> 01:02:16.465
I haven't thought
about her in ages.

01:02:16.467 --> 01:02:20.268
She said, "I hope
you like eating alone."

01:02:20.270 --> 01:02:22.270
Then she slammed the door.

01:02:22.272 --> 01:02:26.742
She was very good
at slamming doors.

01:02:26.744 --> 01:02:30.545
Heh! So, uh...

01:02:30.547 --> 01:02:32.748
You like eating alone?

01:02:32.750 --> 01:02:34.750
I'm not alone.
I've got you.

01:02:34.752 --> 01:02:37.419
My business partner.
Heh!

01:02:37.421 --> 01:02:41.189
Mom slammed doors, too?

01:02:41.558 --> 01:02:42.824
What, are you writing a paper

01:02:42.826 --> 01:02:44.593
On my failed relationships?

01:02:44.595 --> 01:02:46.394
No, uh... thanks.

01:02:46.396 --> 01:02:50.632
I'm just wondering
why you never got
married again.

01:02:53.337 --> 01:02:55.971
I guess I was...

01:02:55.973 --> 01:02:59.341
Looking
for something that I
never quite found.

01:03:00.944 --> 01:03:02.611
Perfection?

01:03:02.613 --> 01:03:06.114
You know, I always
believed in
the perfect match,

01:03:06.116 --> 01:03:07.949
That there was someone out there

01:03:07.951 --> 01:03:09.317
Who'd be exactly what I needed

01:03:09.319 --> 01:03:13.455
And we would sort of
complete each other.

01:03:13.457 --> 01:03:15.323
But you never found her.

01:03:15.325 --> 01:03:19.427
Well, perfection's
a funny thing.

01:03:21.031 --> 01:03:23.298
I mean, look
how perfect this is.

01:03:23.300 --> 01:03:26.868
The way the crystal
captures the light,

01:03:26.870 --> 01:03:30.839
Refracts it
into beautiful patterns.

01:03:33.310 --> 01:03:35.677
Silicon's amazing, isn't it?

01:03:35.679 --> 01:03:39.848
You can mold it into
glass or computer chips,

01:03:39.850 --> 01:03:42.184
But you know what?

01:03:42.186 --> 01:03:43.351
It's not alive.

01:03:43.353 --> 01:03:46.288
And the more you try to find

01:03:46.290 --> 01:03:49.691
That kind of perfection
in people,

01:03:49.693 --> 01:03:54.462
The more meals...
You will eat alone.

01:04:03.240 --> 01:04:05.073
Roscoe:
It's amazing.

01:04:05.075 --> 01:04:08.443
The internet
didn't damage
your pattern at all.

01:04:13.383 --> 01:04:14.883
Roscoe...

01:04:14.885 --> 01:04:17.686
What's it like to feel?

01:04:17.688 --> 01:04:19.187
What's it like to touch?

01:04:19.189 --> 01:04:23.258
I'm not really sure
it's something
you can explain.

01:04:23.260 --> 01:04:24.993
Try?

01:04:24.995 --> 01:04:27.162
Ok.

01:04:29.099 --> 01:04:33.001
Uh, all right.

01:04:33.003 --> 01:04:34.603
Close your eyes.

01:04:34.605 --> 01:04:38.106
Now... Imagine
a dance floor.

01:04:38.108 --> 01:04:41.943
You and and your
partner are dancing
to the beat.

01:04:41.945 --> 01:04:43.445
Hip-hop or rock?

01:04:43.447 --> 01:04:44.279
Oh, it doesn't matter,

01:04:44.281 --> 01:04:47.482
Because suddenly it changes.

01:04:48.585 --> 01:04:50.285
It slows down to a ballad.

01:04:50.287 --> 01:04:52.087
Ok.

01:04:52.089 --> 01:04:54.389
He touches your hair.

01:04:54.391 --> 01:04:56.591
It feels like...

01:04:56.593 --> 01:04:59.561
Like a violin gently playing.

01:04:59.563 --> 01:05:01.062
You touch his cheek.

01:05:01.064 --> 01:05:02.597
It feels like...

01:05:02.599 --> 01:05:05.867
Like a flute
holding a single
quavering note

01:05:05.869 --> 01:05:06.968
High above the rest.

01:05:06.970 --> 01:05:09.738
You put your arms
around each other

01:05:09.740 --> 01:05:12.440
And begin to dance.

01:05:13.143 --> 01:05:17.212
The embrace feels like a cello

01:05:17.214 --> 01:05:20.815
Harmonizing with the violin.

01:05:20.817 --> 01:05:22.817
Ok.

01:05:22.819 --> 01:05:25.020
Now open your eyes.

01:05:30.327 --> 01:05:33.328
There. There.

01:05:33.330 --> 01:05:35.764
You feel that?

01:05:35.766 --> 01:05:38.433
No.

01:05:38.435 --> 01:05:40.635
I can't feel anything.

01:05:43.340 --> 01:05:45.573
That's ok.

01:05:45.575 --> 01:05:47.342
Me, neither.

01:05:47.344 --> 01:05:50.345
Nothing at all.

01:05:52.149 --> 01:05:54.883
Guess you and I never will.

01:05:59.823 --> 01:06:04.359
 If you love me,
you sure show it strange 

01:06:04.361 --> 01:06:09.764
 is there anything
that you wouldn't change? 

01:06:09.766 --> 01:06:16.271
 I can't be
your paper doll 

01:06:16.273 --> 01:06:19.207
 I want to be perfect 

01:06:19.209 --> 01:06:20.542
 but I'm me 

01:06:20.544 --> 01:06:23.311
 I want to be flawless 

01:06:23.313 --> 01:06:24.646
 but you see 

01:06:24.648 --> 01:06:28.550
 every little crack,
every chip, every dent 

01:06:28.552 --> 01:06:33.621
 every little mistake,
oh, yeah 

01:06:33.623 --> 01:06:36.458
 I want to be perfect 

01:06:36.460 --> 01:06:38.226
 just like you 

01:06:38.228 --> 01:06:40.395
 but there's only so much 

01:06:40.397 --> 01:06:42.897
 that a girl can do 

01:06:42.899 --> 01:06:46.835
 when I look in the mirror
what is see 

01:06:46.837 --> 01:06:51.339
 makes sense to me, yeah 

01:06:51.341 --> 01:06:54.409
 perfectly 

01:06:58.248 --> 01:07:02.817
Ok. There's no need
to be nervous.

01:07:02.819 --> 01:07:04.336
I'm fine.

01:07:04.337 --> 01:07:05.854
I mean, just because
he's president
of the record company

01:07:05.856 --> 01:07:08.590
And he's meeting, well,
right now with my boss,

01:07:08.592 --> 01:07:12.527
That's no reason
to be intimidated.

01:07:12.529 --> 01:07:15.263
I'm not.

01:07:15.265 --> 01:07:17.399
Good.

01:07:17.401 --> 01:07:19.000
I've gotta go to the bathroom.

01:07:19.002 --> 01:07:21.169
Again?
Yeah.

01:07:21.171 --> 01:07:23.071
Heh!

01:07:28.278 --> 01:07:29.344
That looks like daryl.

01:07:29.346 --> 01:07:33.415
Roscoe: It is. Back when
he was rapper de fibb.

01:07:33.417 --> 01:07:34.783
He looks so mean.

01:07:34.785 --> 01:07:36.652
Eh, it's all image.

01:07:36.653 --> 01:07:38.520
Ah, that was my debut album.
Went double platinum.

01:07:38.522 --> 01:07:39.788
Barely made a penny, though.

01:07:39.790 --> 01:07:41.589
Harshtone records
got all the money.

01:07:41.591 --> 01:07:43.742
That's not right.

01:07:43.743 --> 01:07:45.894
Maybe not. But every
performer has a choice.

01:07:45.896 --> 01:07:47.629
Weldon giles
offered me a contract.

01:07:47.631 --> 01:07:49.798
It was my choice to sign it.

01:07:49.799 --> 01:07:51.966
I'm glad I don't
have to worry about
things like money.

01:07:51.968 --> 01:07:54.619
Or meetings.

01:07:54.620 --> 01:07:57.271
Mr. Giles would prefer
that loretta wasn't
in our discussion.

01:07:57.274 --> 01:07:59.207
Giles:
You and your son

01:07:59.209 --> 01:08:01.743
Have revolutionized
the music industry.

01:08:01.745 --> 01:08:03.144
You've given it new life.

01:08:03.146 --> 01:08:05.413
Loretta modern's
on her way to being
a household name.

01:08:05.415 --> 01:08:08.616
Skygraph's entering
into a partnership
with harshtone, xander.

01:08:08.618 --> 01:08:11.286
With you spearheading
the new division.

01:08:11.288 --> 01:08:13.455
Heh! I... I don't know
what to say.

01:08:13.457 --> 01:08:15.957
We will corner the market
on holographic performers.

01:08:15.959 --> 01:08:17.792
You don't have to
pay 'em, you don't
have to feed 'em,

01:08:17.794 --> 01:08:21.229
And when
they're not on stage,
you can put 'em away.

01:08:21.231 --> 01:08:22.930
That's the kind of
performer I like.

01:08:22.933 --> 01:08:25.934
How are
the holograms gonna
feel about that?

01:08:25.935 --> 01:08:28.069
Uh...

01:08:32.274 --> 01:08:33.808
Funny kid.

01:08:33.810 --> 01:08:35.477
Roscoe, I'm giving
you and your father

01:08:35.479 --> 01:08:38.680
Free creative rein
to develop new holographic
personalities.

01:08:38.682 --> 01:08:40.915
In the meantime,
we'll exploit
the one we've got.

01:08:40.917 --> 01:08:42.917
What do you mean
the one you've got?

01:08:42.919 --> 01:08:45.487
We purchased loretta
from skygraph.

01:08:45.488 --> 01:08:48.156
No. They can't
just buy her.

01:08:48.158 --> 01:08:51.292
Well, they purchase
computer programs
all the time.

01:08:51.294 --> 01:08:52.460
Yeah, it looks like
they bought you, too.

01:08:52.462 --> 01:08:54.362
Roscoe, I know
loretta might seem

01:08:54.363 --> 01:08:56.430
Like an individual,
but she's not.

01:08:56.433 --> 01:08:57.265
Then what is she?

01:08:57.267 --> 01:09:00.535
Property. And now
she's my property,

01:09:00.537 --> 01:09:01.301
Plain and simple.

01:09:01.304 --> 01:09:03.337
Roscoe, let's just step outside

01:09:03.340 --> 01:09:04.506
And talk calmly about this.

01:09:04.506 --> 01:09:05.673
Yeah, I know. Like
business partners.

01:09:05.675 --> 01:09:08.042
But you know what?
I'm not your
business partner.

01:09:08.044 --> 01:09:08.943
I'm your son.

01:09:08.944 --> 01:09:12.147
Ahem. We have
the ability

01:09:12.149 --> 01:09:14.349
To create lorettas
of every ethnicity...

01:09:14.350 --> 01:09:16.384
Asian, african american,
hispanic.

01:09:16.386 --> 01:09:18.386
Giles:
It's brilliant...
No.

01:09:18.388 --> 01:09:21.356
We'll mold loretta
into whatever
we want her to be.

01:09:21.358 --> 01:09:24.392
Isn't that right, xander?

01:09:25.694 --> 01:09:27.194
Xander?

01:09:27.197 --> 01:09:29.564
Y-yes.

01:09:29.566 --> 01:09:32.200
Yes, we can do all of that.

01:09:32.202 --> 01:09:36.237
But just because
we can doesn't mean
that we should.

01:09:37.307 --> 01:09:39.240
I'm sorry, but I'm
with my son on this.

01:09:39.242 --> 01:09:43.377
Whether loretta
is a person
or a program,

01:09:43.380 --> 01:09:46.381
She deserves
to be treated
with dignity.

01:09:47.050 --> 01:09:48.383
Fine.

01:09:48.385 --> 01:09:52.487
I'll set up a task force
on hologram ethics.

01:09:52.488 --> 01:09:55.423
Daryl, could you please
take the data cell?

01:09:57.327 --> 01:09:58.793
Now.

01:10:02.832 --> 01:10:04.966
I'm sorry, roscoe.

01:10:05.402 --> 01:10:07.268
It's not fair.

01:10:07.270 --> 01:10:08.436
I need security in here.

01:10:08.438 --> 01:10:10.338
Xander, talk
to your son.
Come on!

01:10:10.340 --> 01:10:13.041
You know, for once
that's exactly what
I intend to do.

01:10:13.043 --> 01:10:15.043
How could you let him do this?

01:10:15.045 --> 01:10:17.779
You said every performer
has a choice.

01:10:17.781 --> 01:10:20.949
How about loretta?
Where's her choice?

01:10:20.951 --> 01:10:24.018
All right, sir, let's go.

01:10:27.057 --> 01:10:29.891
I want that under lock and key.

01:10:29.893 --> 01:10:32.860
We won't let them
get away with it.
You created loretta.

01:10:32.862 --> 01:10:36.364
We won't let them
do this to you
or to her.

01:10:38.568 --> 01:10:41.402
What is it?

01:10:41.404 --> 01:10:43.605
Nothing.

01:10:43.907 --> 01:10:46.808
Hey, dad, if I were to tell you

01:10:46.810 --> 01:10:48.409
How proud I was to be your son,

01:10:48.411 --> 01:10:50.912
Would you get all mushy on me?

01:10:50.914 --> 01:10:53.381
Who me? No.

01:10:53.383 --> 01:10:55.250
Good, good.

01:10:55.252 --> 01:10:58.720
'cause, uh, I am proud.

01:11:03.093 --> 01:11:05.610
Dad!

01:11:05.611 --> 01:11:08.128
Xander: Whoa! I'm ok,
I'm ok! I'm done.

01:11:12.602 --> 01:11:14.969
Where am I? Roscoe?

01:11:14.971 --> 01:11:17.505
You have a decision
to make, loretta.

01:11:17.507 --> 01:11:21.309
Roscoe can't
make it for you,
neither can I.

01:11:21.311 --> 01:11:24.279
On the one hand,
you can stay here.

01:11:24.281 --> 01:11:26.247
If you do, harshtone
will own you.

01:11:26.249 --> 01:11:28.182
You'll perform
when they tell you.

01:11:28.184 --> 01:11:31.119
All I want to do is perform.

01:11:31.121 --> 01:11:34.322
Then maybe this is
where you belong.

01:11:34.324 --> 01:11:38.293
But then on the other hand.

01:11:38.295 --> 01:11:39.193
Your handheld.

01:11:39.195 --> 01:11:42.297
With wireless web.

01:11:42.299 --> 01:11:44.799
I uploaded once.

01:11:44.801 --> 01:11:47.335
The choice is yours.

01:11:47.871 --> 01:11:49.504
Giles: Fibbs,
are you in there?

01:11:49.506 --> 01:11:52.840
I hope you're taking
good care of my girl.

01:11:58.181 --> 01:11:59.814
Daryl, voice-over:
"dear mr. Giles,

01:11:59.816 --> 01:12:01.482
"after careful consideration,

01:12:01.484 --> 01:12:02.517
"I've decided to free myself

01:12:02.519 --> 01:12:04.218
"from you and harshtone records.

01:12:04.220 --> 01:12:06.954
"I believe our friend
loretta modern

01:12:06.956 --> 01:12:09.123
Has chosen to do the same."

01:12:09.125 --> 01:12:12.894
Sincerely, daryl j. Fibbs."

01:12:19.169 --> 01:12:21.235
Heh! Ha ha!

01:12:26.576 --> 01:12:28.076
You again?

01:12:28.078 --> 01:12:29.877
Mm-hmm.

01:12:29.879 --> 01:12:31.579
Where to this time?

01:12:31.581 --> 01:12:34.182
Anywhere but here.

01:12:34.184 --> 01:12:37.385
4,200,708 matches.

01:12:37.387 --> 01:12:39.287
Ha ha ha!

01:12:58.274 --> 01:12:59.674
Roscoe... ow!

